# ============================================================
# vibe-economics — Data Source Wishlist
# ============================================================
# How to use this file:
#   1. Copy values you have into your .env (never commit keys).
#   2. For each source: sign up at the URL in the comment, paste key below.
#   3. Tell Claude the var name you set — the catalog api_key: field must match exactly.
#
# Legend:
#   [FREE]        No key required, no cost
#   [FREE KEY]    Free signup, key required; rate limits noted
#   [FREEMIUM]    Free tier exists but useful tier costs money
#   [PAID]        No meaningful free tier / enterprise only
#   [UNOFFICIAL]  No official API; scraping / undocumented endpoint
#   ✅            Already working in environment
#   ⚠️            Empty / not yet provisioned
#   🔜            Not yet in catalog; needs wiring
#
# Already provisioned (from ticket 0006):
#   BEA_API_KEY           ✅  working
#   BLS_API_KEY           ✅  working
#   ALPHAVANTAGE_API_KEY  ✅  set but untested (25 req/day — very tight, cache hard)
#   FRED_API_KEY          ⚠️  empty — needs real 32-char value
#   CENSUS_API_KEY        ⚠️  empty — needed by median-income service (ticket 0007)
#   NASDAQ_DATA_LINK_API_KEY  ⚠️  empty
# ============================================================


# ============================================================
# HOUSING MARKET
# ============================================================

# --- Zillow Research Data ---
# [FREE] Bulk CSV/XLSX downloads, no API key.
# Time series: ZHVI (home values), ZORI (rents), inventory, days-on-market, price cuts.
# City / metro / zip / county breakdown. Updated monthly.
# Download index: https://www.zillow.com/research/data/
# No API; acquire by direct URL to each CSV.
# Notes: license allows non-commercial research; cite Zillow Research. No redistribution.
# Env var: not applicable (key-free URL downloads)
# Suggested catalog id: zillow_zhvi, zillow_zori
# ZILLOW_LICENSE_NOTE="non-commercial, cite Zillow Research"

# --- Redfin Data Center ---
# [FREE] Bulk CSV downloads, no API key.
# Weekly/monthly: median sale price, sale-to-list ratio, homes sold, pending sales,
# new listings, days on market, migration trends. City / metro / zip / state.
# Download index: https://www.redfin.com/news/data-center/
# Notes: Redfin terms allow research use; cite Redfin. No redistribution.
# Suggested catalog id: redfin_market
# REDFIN_LICENSE_NOTE="research use, cite Redfin"

# --- HUD USER (Dept. of Housing & Urban Development) ---
# [FREE KEY] Fair Market Rents (FMR), Income Limits, CHAS (housing affordability),
# American Housing Survey. Metro-level rent benchmarks used by Section 8.
# API: https://www.huduser.gov/portal/dataset/fmr-api.html
# Signup: https://www.huduser.gov/hudapi/public/register
HUD_API_KEY=

# --- ATTOM Property Data ---
# [PAID] Property details, AVM (automated valuation), sales history, tax assessments.
# The gold-standard for granular US property data. Enterprise pricing.
# API docs: https://api.attomdata.com/
# Notes: expensive; only if a service genuinely needs parcel-level data.
ATTOM_API_KEY=

# --- CoreLogic / Black Knight (ICE Mortgage Technology) ---
# [PAID] Enterprise property analytics, MLS-level data, mortgage performance.
# CoreLogic: https://www.corelogic.com/data-and-analytics/
# No self-serve signup; sales process required.
# Notes: consider only if bulk housing analysis needs deeds / liens / distress data.
CORELOGIC_API_KEY=


# ============================================================
# EMPLOYMENT
# ============================================================

# --- BLS (Bureau of Labor Statistics) ---
# [FREE KEY] ✅  Already working (BLS_API_KEY)
# CPI, employment, wages, JOLTS, unemployment, PPI, productivity.
# v2 API: 500 queries/day, up to 50 series per query.
# Signup: https://data.bls.gov/registrationEngine/
BLS_API_KEY=

# --- ADP National Employment Report ---
# [FREE] Monthly payroll employment data by sector and size.
# Machine-readable data released as Excel/CSV on release day.
# No API; direct download from: https://adpemploymentreport.com/
# The "Research Institute" arm publishes datasets:
# https://research.adp.com/data-products/
# Suggested catalog id: adp_employment
# ADPRI_LICENSE_NOTE="free for research, cite ADP Research Institute"

# --- Indeed Hiring Lab ---
# [FREE] Job postings index, job seeker activity, wage tracker.
# Research datasets: https://www.hiringlab.org/
# No formal API; bulk datasets available via partnership/request.
# Public charts: https://www.hiringlab.org/data/
# INDEED_LICENSE_NOTE="research use, cite Indeed Hiring Lab"

# --- Challenger, Gray & Christmas Job Cuts ---
# [FREE limited] Monthly announced layoffs by sector (press release).
# Historical data available via purchase; recent data free via press release.
# https://www.challengergray.com/research/job-cut-reports/
# No machine-readable API. Acquire by scraping/parsing press releases.
# Notes: useful for leading indicator of employment stress.

# --- LinkedIn Economic Graph ---
# [PAID / partnership] Hiring rates, skills demand, workforce migration.
# Academic partnerships exist but no public API.
# https://economicgraph.linkedin.com/
# Notes: most data is behind a partnership; some aggregate reports are public.


# ============================================================
# INTERNATIONAL TRADE & DEVELOPMENT
# ============================================================

# --- UN Comtrade Plus ---
# [FREE KEY] Official UN bilateral trade statistics (imports/exports by commodity, country, year).
# One of the best sources for granular country-level trade flows.
# Free tier: 500 requests/hour with key; bulk datasets available for download.
# API docs: https://comtradeplus.un.org/
# Signup: https://comtradeplus.un.org/  (create account → API subscription → free tier)
# Suggested catalog id: un_comtrade
UN_COMTRADE_API_KEY=

# --- WTO Stats ---
# [FREE] WTO trade statistics: tariff data, merchandise trade, commercial services.
# API: https://apiportal.wto.org/
# Key-free for most datasets; some endpoints need free registration.
# Signup: https://apiportal.wto.org/
WTO_API_KEY=

# --- UNCTAD (UN Conference on Trade and Development) ---
# [FREE] Trade, investment, maritime, commodity, development indicators.
# UNCTADStat API: https://unctadstat.unctad.org/datacentre/
# Key-free JSON/CSV bulk downloads. No rate limit documented.
# Suggested catalog id: unctad_stats
# UNCTAD_LICENSE_NOTE="CC BY 3.0 IGO, cite UNCTAD"

# --- Asian Development Bank (ADB) Key Indicators ---
# [FREE] GDP, poverty, infrastructure, finance for 49 Asia-Pacific economies.
# API: https://kidb.adb.org/
# Key-free; JSON/CSV. Annual data, good developing-Asia coverage.
# Suggested catalog id: adb_indicators

# --- African Development Bank (AfDB) Statistics ---
# [FREE] Socio-economic data for African countries.
# Open Data Portal: https://dataportal.opendataforafrica.org/
# Key-free; SDMX/JSON.
# Notes: useful for structured access to African national statistics.
# Suggested catalog id: afdb_stats

# --- IMF Direction of Trade Statistics (DOTS) ---
# [FREE] Bilateral trade flows for ~190 countries.
# Part of the IMF Data API: https://www.imf.org/en/Data
# Key-free JSON.
# Suggested catalog id: imf_dots

# --- CEPII BACI (Bilateral Trade Database) ---
# [FREE] Harmonised bilateral trade flows at the HS6 product level.
# http://www.cepii.fr/CEPII/en/bdd_modele/bdd_modele_item.asp?id=37
# Free bulk download after free registration; annual CSV. Very large files.
# Notes: the cleanest global bilateral trade dataset; recommended over Comtrade for analysis.
# CEPII_LICENSE_NOTE="free for research, cite CEPII"

# --- World Bank WITS (World Integrated Trade Solution) ---
# [FREE] Tariff and trade data integrating COMTRADE, UNCTAD, WTO.
# API: https://wits.worldbank.org/witsapiintro.aspx
# Key-free. Good for tariff rates and NTMs.
# Suggested catalog id: wits_trade


# ============================================================
# COMMODITIES & ENERGY
# ============================================================

# --- EIA (US Energy Information Administration) ---
# [FREE KEY] Oil, gas, coal, electricity production/consumption/prices for US and global.
# Free, comprehensive, official. ~5,000 series.
# Rate limit: 5,000 req/hour with key.
# API docs: https://www.eia.gov/opendata/
# Signup: https://www.eia.gov/opendata/register.php
# Suggested catalog id: eia_energy
EIA_API_KEY=

# --- World Bank Pink Sheet Commodities ---
# [FREE] Monthly commodity prices (energy, metals, agriculture) since 1960.
# Direct Excel download from World Bank; no key needed.
# URL: https://thedocs.worldbank.org/en/doc/5d903e848db1d1b83e0ec8f744e55570-0350012021/related/CMO-Pink-Sheet-October-2024.xlsx
# (URL changes monthly — acquire from the Pink Sheet landing page)
# Suggested catalog id: wb_pink_sheet

# --- OPEC Data / MOMR ---
# [FREE] Monthly Oil Market Report — supply, demand, prices, stocks.
# https://www.opec.org/opec_web/en/publications/338.htm
# PDF/Excel; no API. Acquire via direct download links.
# Suggested catalog id: opec_momr

# --- LME (London Metal Exchange) ---
# [FREEMIUM] Base metal prices (copper, aluminium, zinc, etc.).
# Free delayed/historical data via LME website; real-time is paid.
# https://www.lme.com/Market-data
# Notes: for historical commodity prices, World Bank Pink Sheet is easier.

# --- CME Group DataMine ---
# [PAID] Futures and options data (oil, gold, grains, currencies, rates).
# https://www.cmegroup.com/market-data/datamine-historical-data.html
# Notes: expensive; use for high-frequency commodity futures. Pink Sheet fine for macro.

# --- TradingEconomics ---
# [PAID / very limited free] 300k indicators across 196 countries: GDP, inflation,
# trade, commodities, markets. Excellent breadth.
# API: https://tradingeconomics.com/api/
# Free tier: 10 API calls (essentially a demo only).
# Pricing: from ~$50/month for limited access; full access much more.
# Notes: the breadth is compelling for comparative international macro.
# Worth paying if a specific service (e.g. cross-country commodity tracker) truly needs it.
TRADING_ECONOMICS_API_KEY=

# --- Quandl / Nasdaq Data Link — Commodities ---
# [FREE KEY ⚠️] CHRIS series (continuous futures), ODA (IMF commodity prices), etc.
# Free tier with key. See STOCKS section for full details.
NASDAQ_DATA_LINK_API_KEY=


# ============================================================
# EQUITIES & FINANCIAL MARKETS
# ============================================================

# --- Alpha Vantage ---
# [FREE KEY ✅] Equities (US + global), FX, crypto, technical indicators, fundamentals.
# Free: 25 requests/day, 5/minute. Severely limited — cache every response.
# Standard tier (~$50/mo): 75/min, no daily cap.
# Signup: https://www.alphavantage.co/support/#api-key
ALPHAVANTAGE_API_KEY=

# --- Nasdaq Data Link (formerly Quandl) ---
# [FREE KEY ⚠️] Large library of financial and economic datasets.
# Free tier includes: FRED (mirror), World Bank, OECD, IMF, ODA commodity prices,
# CHRIS continuous futures, Zacks fundamentals (partial).
# Premium datasets (e.g. full Zacks, Sharadar) require paid subscription.
# Signup: https://data.nasdaq.com/sign-up
# Suggested catalog id: nasdaq_data_link
NASDAQ_DATA_LINK_API_KEY=

# --- Polygon.io ---
# [FREEMIUM 🔜] US equities, options, forex, crypto.
# Free tier: previous-day data only, 5 calls/minute, unlimited historical (delayed).
# Starter ($29/mo): 15-min delayed; Developer ($79/mo): real-time.
# Best free tier for US stock fundamentals and broad ticker coverage.
# Signup: https://polygon.io/
# Suggested catalog id: polygon_stocks
POLYGON_API_KEY=

# --- Finnhub ---
# [FREE KEY 🔜] Real-time + historical stocks, earnings, news, economic data.
# Free tier: 60 calls/minute, 30 years history, fundamentals, insider transactions.
# Very generous free tier for fundamental/macro research.
# Signup: https://finnhub.io/register
# Suggested catalog id: finnhub
FINNHUB_API_KEY=

# --- Tiingo ---
# [FREE KEY 🔜] End-of-day US stocks, ETFs, mutual funds. News API. IEX real-time.
# Free tier: 500 requests/hour, up to 50 tickers/request, full history.
# Excellent for long-run total-return series; cheaper than most alternatives.
# Signup: https://www.tiingo.com/
# Suggested catalog id: tiingo_eod
TIINGO_API_KEY=

# --- IEX Cloud ---
# [FREEMIUM] US equity data: real-time, historical, fundamentals, news.
# Free "Sandbox" environment exists but uses fake data.
# Paid: starts ~$9/mo (500K credits). Real historical + fundamentals ~$29/mo+.
# https://iexcloud.io/
# Notes: solid quality but paid tiers may not be worth it vs Tiingo + Polygon.
IEXCLOUD_API_KEY=

# --- Yahoo Finance ---
# [UNOFFICIAL / FREE] Global equities, ETFs, FX, crypto — excellent breadth.
# No official API; yfinance Python library uses undocumented endpoint.
# Subject to rate limiting and potential ToS issues; use for exploration, not production.
# No key needed.
# Notes: yfinance is the go-to for quick backtests; unreliable for automated pipelines.

# --- Bloomberg Terminal / Bloomberg Data License ---
# [PAID enterprise] The gold standard for financial data.
# Terminal: ~$24k/year. Data License API: enterprise contract.
# https://www.bloomberg.com/professional/product/data-license/
# Notes: overkill for research; provision only if a service needs real-time Bloomberg data.
BLOOMBERG_API_KEY=

# --- Refinitiv / LSEG Data Platform ---
# [PAID enterprise] Formerly Thomson Reuters. Comparable to Bloomberg.
# https://developers.lseg.com/
# Notes: enterprise tier; LSEG also owns Yield Book, FTSE.
REFINITIV_APP_KEY=

# --- Seeking Alpha ---
# [FREEMIUM / unofficial] Premium analysis, earnings transcripts, quant ratings.
# No official public API. Premium subscription scraping exists but violates ToS.
# Unofficial API used by some open-source projects — fragile and ToS-gray.
# Notes: not recommended as a stable pipeline source.

# --- OpenBB ---
# [FREE / open-source] Financial terminal aggregating many free + paid data providers.
# Not a data source itself, but can route to many of the above.
# https://openbb.co/
# Notes: useful for exploration; not a data pipeline.


# ============================================================
# CENTRAL BANKS & BROAD MACRO
# ============================================================

# --- FRED (St. Louis Fed) ---
# [FREE KEY ⚠️] 800k+ time series: macro, financial, regional, international.
# 120 requests/minute, no daily cap.
# Signup: https://fred.stlouisfed.org/docs/api/api_key.html
FRED_API_KEY=

# --- ECB Statistical Data Warehouse ---
# [FREE] Euro area monetary/financial statistics, exchange rates, inflation.
# API: https://data-api.ecb.europa.eu/
# Key-free SDMX/JSON. Excellent for EUR area macro.
# Suggested catalog id: ecb_sdw

# --- Bank of England ---
# [FREE] UK monetary/financial statistics, interest rates, exchange rates, GDP.
# API: https://www.bankofengland.co.uk/boeapps/database/
# Key-free; CSV/JSON via the Statistical Interactive Database.
# Suggested catalog id: boe_stats

# --- Bank for International Settlements (BIS) ---
# [FREE] FX turnover, international banking stats, debt securities, property prices,
# effective exchange rates, credit gaps.
# Bulk data: https://www.bis.org/statistics/full_data_sets.htm
# Key-free CSV/ZIP downloads; no rate limit.
# Suggested catalog id: bis_stats

# --- Reserve Bank of Australia ---
# [FREE] Australian monetary/financial statistics.
# https://www.rba.gov.au/statistics/
# Key-free CSV/Excel. Good for AUD rates + Australian housing.
# Suggested catalog id: rba_stats

# --- Statistics Canada ---
# [FREE KEY] Canadian national accounts, labour, prices.
# API: https://www.statcan.gc.ca/en/developers/wds
# Free; requires free registration for higher limits.
# Suggested catalog id: statcan
STATCAN_API_KEY=

# --- Eurostat (EU) ---
# [FREE] ✅  Already in catalog (key-free SDMX API)
# Suggested catalog id: eurostat


# ============================================================
# ALTERNATIVE & CREATIVE SOURCES
# ============================================================

# --- Google Trends (via Pytrends) ---
# [FREE / unofficial] Search interest as economic sentiment proxy.
# PyPI: pytrends — unofficial Python library for Google Trends.
# No API key; rate-limited by Google (avoid tight loops; ~1 req/5s).
# Use cases: recession fear index, real estate search interest, consumer sentiment.
# Notes: completely free; powerful leading indicator. Not an official API.

# --- CoinGecko ---
# [FREE / FREEMIUM] Crypto prices, market caps, DeFi, on-chain metrics.
# Free tier: 30 calls/min, no key needed (Demo key expands slightly).
# Pro: $129/mo+.
# API: https://www.coingecko.com/en/api
# Suggested catalog id: coingecko
COINGECKO_API_KEY=

# --- Glassnode ---
# [FREEMIUM] On-chain crypto analytics: HODL waves, exchange flows, miner revenue.
# Free tier: some metrics with limited history.
# Standard $39/mo unlocks most metrics.
# API: https://glassnode.com/api
GLASSNODE_API_KEY=

# --- Our World in Data ---
# [FREE] Long-run data on GDP, poverty, health, education, inequality, energy.
# GitHub repo: https://github.com/owid/owid-datasets
# No API; CSV/TSV direct from GitHub. Very clean, well-documented.
# Notes: great for multi-decade context; some series go back centuries.
# Suggested catalog id: owid

# --- Opportunity Insights (Harvard/Raj Chetty) ---
# [FREE] US intergenerational mobility, opportunity gaps by geography.
# Data: https://opportunityinsights.org/data/
# No key; direct CSV download.
# Notes: extraordinary dataset for inequality/mobility analysis.
# Suggested catalog id: opportunity_insights

# --- NBER Macrohistory Database ---
# [FREE] US pre-WWII macro data (industrial production, prices, money, 1867–1961).
# https://www.nber.org/research/data/nber-macrohistory-database
# No key; direct download.
# Notes: pairs well with JST for pre-war US series.
# Suggested catalog id: nber_macrohistory

# --- Open Street Map / Overpass API ---
# [FREE] Geocoding, business counts, land use, infrastructure density.
# Overpass API: https://overpass-api.de/
# Key-free but fair-use. Useful for spatial economic questions.
# Notes: slow for large queries; use Overpass Turbo to prototype.

# --- NASA Earthdata / Copernicus ---
# [FREE KEY] Satellite imagery, night-light data (proxy for economic activity),
# agricultural conditions, sea surface temperatures.
# NASA LAADS: https://ladsweb.modaps.eosdis.nasa.gov/
# Free with registration.
# Notes: night-light data from VIIRS is a classic GDP proxy for ungoverned regions.
NASA_EARTHDATA_TOKEN=

# --- PriceStats / Billion Prices Project (MIT) ---
# [RESEARCH] Online price scraping for real-time inflation tracking.
# Academic access only; commercial product via State Street.
# http://www.pricestats.com/
# Notes: interesting methodology; not publicly accessible.

# --- Numbeo ---
# [PAID ⚠️] City cost-of-living: rent, groceries, transport, healthcare.
# Already in catalog; capture existing key if provisioned.
# https://www.numbeo.com/api/
NUMBEO_API_KEY=


# ============================================================
# UNSTRUCTURED / DOCUMENT-BASED INTERNATIONAL STATS
# ============================================================
# These are official but come as PDFs / inconsistent formats.
# A future "pdf-ingest" skill would be needed to parse them.
# Examples noted by maintainer:
#   Ethiopia ESS trade stats: https://ess.gov.et/ (PDF/Excel releases)
#   National stats offices: Kenya KNBS, Nigeria NBS, Ghana GSS, Tanzania NBS
#   ASEAN Stats: https://www.aseanstats.org/
#   SADC stats: https://www.sadc.int/tools-and-publication/databases/sadc-statistics/
#
# Recommended approach (see ticket 0009):
#   1. Build a lightweight PDF→structured-data skill that extracts tabular data
#      from consistent report templates.
#   2. Maintain a "national stats offices" registry (country → PDF release URL pattern)
#   3. For major African/Asian stats offices, check if XLSX version exists alongside PDF.
#
# No env vars needed — it's a parsing/acquisition skill problem, not a key problem.


# ============================================================
# REGIONAL PRICE PARITIES & COST OF LIVING
# ============================================================

# --- BEA Regional Price Parities ---
# [FREE KEY ✅] US metro/state price levels relative to national average.
# Already served via BEA_API_KEY (SARPP table).
# BEA_API_KEY= (see above)

# --- Census / American Community Survey ---
# [FREE KEY ⚠️] Detailed demographics, income, housing, commuting. 5-year ACS.
# CENSUS_API_KEY= (see main provisioning section in ticket 0006)
CENSUS_API_KEY=

# --- Glassdoor / levels.fyi ---
# [UNOFFICIAL] Salary data by role, company, location.
# No public API. Glassdoor had a partner API (discontinued).
# levels.fyi exports are informal.
# Notes: not reliable as a data pipeline.


# ============================================================
# FOLLOWUP: KEYS TO PROVISION FIRST
# ============================================================
# Priority order (free, high value, already partially wired):
#   1. FRED_API_KEY          — free 32-char key; unblocks huge macro breadth
#   2. CENSUS_API_KEY        — free; needed by median-income service NOW (ticket 0007)
#   3. EIA_API_KEY           — free; unlocks all energy/commodity data
#   4. UN_COMTRADE_API_KEY   — free; best trade-flow data globally
#   5. FINNHUB_API_KEY       — free, generous; stock fundamentals
#   6. TIINGO_API_KEY        — free, good; long-run equity total returns
#   7. POLYGON_API_KEY       — free delayed; US market breadth
#   8. HUD_API_KEY           — free; housing rent benchmarks
#
# Worth paying (if a specific service needs it):
#   9. TRADING_ECONOMICS_API_KEY  — $50+/mo; exceptional international breadth
#  10. NUMBEO_API_KEY             — ~$50/mo; city cost-of-living detail
#  11. POLYGON paid tier          — $29/mo; 15-min delayed US data
#  12. FINNHUB paid tier          — more tick data if needed
#
# Not worth it unless you have a very specific need:
#   - BLOOMBERG_API_KEY / REFINITIV_APP_KEY  (enterprise, very expensive)
#   - ATTOM_API_KEY / CORELOGIC_API_KEY      (enterprise property data)
